        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 4:50AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 450 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Baird, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Putnam, Mccarty Lake, Clyde, Baird, Eula, Admiral, Us-283 Near The
Callahan-Shackelford County Line, Moran, Ibex, Albany, and Us-180
Near The Shackelford-Stephens County Line.

This includes Interstate 20 between Mile Markers 294 and 320.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
